{"type":"message","id":"d74dedff","parentId":"8008d45e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:35:48.789Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_drzio96k8r0x_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 113516\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n3. Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe CFI analysis was just completed. The natural next step is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would compare using CFI scores as weights vs just frequency for compression, and evaluate which produces better next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that I can work with:\r\n- research/CFI_RESULTS.md - the CFI analysis\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n- pulse.ps1\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment design document for the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would be a concrete action that advances toward the pending goal.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concise experiment design file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have low CFI scores, suggesting frequency-based compression is mostly capturing metaprogramming noise rather than causal research trajectories. A controlled experiment is needed to validate whether CFI-weighted compression outperforms frequency-only approaches.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a concrete experiment design for the CFI-weighted compression comparison, specifying hypothesis, methodology, metrics, and implementation approach.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** DESIGN PHASE  \r\n**Depends on:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nCFI-weighted compression will produce better next-pulse prediction fidelity than frequency-only compression because it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI≈0) while preserving true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Two Compression Variants\r\n\r\n| Variant | Weight Function | Rationale |\r\n|---------|-----------------|-----------|\r\n| **Freq-B-only** | w(f) = f | Baseline from CFI_RESULTS.md |\r\n| **CFI-weighted** | w(f, cfi) = f × cfi | Prioritizes causal persistence |\r\n\r\n### Compression Operation\r\nFor each invariant token sequence:\r\n```\r\ncompressed_weight = sum(weight(token_i for token_i in sequence))\r\nthreshold = top-k by weight (k = 20% of total invariants)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metrics\r\n\r\n1. **Prediction Accuracy**: Reconstruct \"expected next state\" from compressed representation\r\n   - Compare file list predictions (what should exist next pulse)\r\n   - Compare content predictions (what changes to tracked files)\r\n\r\n2. **Compression Ratio**: Original invariants → retained invariants\r\n   - Track both count and cumulative weight preserved\r\n\r\n3. **Signal-to-Noise Ratio**: CFI≥0.7 invariants in compressed set\r\n   - Higher = better filtering of metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n\r\n```\r\nexperiments/\r\n  cfi_compression/\r\n    compress_freq.py      # Frequency-only compression\r\n    compress_cfi.py       # CFI-weighted compression  \r\n    evaluate.py           # Compare predictions vs actual next state\r\n    results.md            # Experiment output\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n\r\n| Metric | Freq-B-only | CFI-weighted |\r\n|--------|-------------|--------------|\r\n| Prediction accuracy | ~60% | >75% |\r\n| CFI≥0.7 in set | ~5.7% | >40% |\r\n| Compression ratio | 80%→20% | 80%→20% |\r\n\r\n### Next Steps\r\n\r\n1. [ ] Implement `experiments/cfi_compression/compress_freq.py`\r\n2. [ ] Implement `experiments/cfi_compression/compress_cfi.py`\r\n3. [ ] Run both on current invariants\r\n4. [ ] Compare predictions to actual next pulse state\r\n5. [ ] Document results in `experiments/cfi_compression/results.md`\r\nfile: experiments/cfi_compression/EXPERIMENT_DESIGN.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:35:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366548786}}
